Greek Socialist Lawmaker Won’t Vote for Austerity Plan, Sky Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-06-28T01:48:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-28/greek-socialist-lawmaker-won-t-vote-for-austerity-plan-sky-says.html
Greek lawmaker Alexandros
Athanasiadis, a member of the ruling Socialist party, said he
told Prime Minister  George Papandreou  he would vote against the
government’s austerity measures unless plans to sell state-owned
energy company PPC and the Athens Water and Sewage Treatment
Company are dropped, Sky News reported, citing an interview.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 